# Wine Platform Middleware

TypeScript Turborepo: middleware connecting Commerce7, OrderPort, and WithWine to Framer storefronts.

## Layout
- `packages/core` — types, `defineConfig`, `PlatformAdapter`, errors (no platform code).
- `packages/adapter-commerce7` / `packages/adapter-orderport` / `packages/adapter-withwine` — implement `PlatformAdapter`; depend only on `core`.
- `packages/framer` — Framer origin/token/CORS access control + product serializer; depends only on `core`, framework-agnostic.
- `apps/*` — thin Vercel consumers; config + API proxies only.

## Rules
- Config schema only in `packages/core/src/config.schema.ts`.
- Adapters map platform responses to core types; throw `PlatformError` from core.
- Framer-facing routes use `packages/framer` for security/serialization; don't re-implement per app.
- New consumer apps: copy `apps/template-withwine` (Next.js — required by the WithWine SDK; works for other platforms too). No business logic in apps.

See root `.cursorrules` for full detail.
